Description:

**Background:**
Reference: oh-my-pi TUI todo renderer. Maps TodoPanelData to displayable
Lines with markers per status.

**Approach:**
In crates/jcode-tui/src/tui/components/todo_panel.rs:
```rust
pub fn render_panel(data: &TodoPanelData, width: usize) -> Vec<Line> {
    let mut lines = Vec::new();
    let title = match data.mode {
        TodoPanelMode::Active => "Todos",
        TodoPanelMode::AllCompletedClear => "Todos (all done)",
    };
    lines.push(Line::styled(format!("── {title} ──"), "dim"));
    if data.visible.is_empty() {
        lines.push(Line::styled("  (no todos)", "dim"));
        return lines;
    }
    for t in &data.visible {
        let marker = match t.status {
            TodoStatus::Completed => "✓",
            TodoStatus::InProgress => "→",
            TodoStatus::Pending => "○",
            TodoStatus::Blocked => "⊘",
        };
        let style = match t.status {
            TodoStatus::Completed => "muted",
            TodoStatus::InProgress => "accent",
            TodoStatus::Pending => "dim",
            TodoStatus::Blocked => "error",
        };
        let active = t.active_form.as_deref().unwrap_or(&t.content);
        lines.push(Line::styled(format!("  {marker} {active}"), style));
    }
    if data.hidden_open_count > 0 {
        lines.push(Line::styled(format!("  +{} more", data.hidden_open_count), "dim"));
    }
    lines
}
```

**Success Criteria:**
- Renders correct marker per status
- Uses active_form when present, falls back to content
- Truncates long text to width
- Shows "+N more" when hidden_open_count > 0
- Empty state shows "(no todos)"

**Test Plan:**
- Unit: render_panel_active_mode_uses_active_form
- Unit: render_panel_falls_back_to_content
- Unit: render_panel_truncates_long_text
- Unit: render_panel_shows_more_hint
- Unit: render_panel_empty_state
- Benchmark: render_panel_5_todos_80_cols < 50µs

**Considerations:**
- Use existing Line/Style types from crates/jcode-tui-render (verify import path)
- Width-aware truncation via truncate_to_width helper if available

Description:

**Background:**
Reference: oh-my-pi selectStickyTodoWindow. Determines which subset of todos
to show in the sticky panel given the constraint of limited vertical space
(maxVisible = 5).

**Approach:**
New file: crates/jcode-tui/src/tui/components/todo_panel.rs

```rust
pub struct TodoPanelData {
    pub visible: Vec<TodoItem>,
    pub hidden_open_count: usize,
    pub mode: TodoPanelMode,
}

pub fn select_sticky_window(todos: &[TodoItem]) -> TodoPanelData {
    let open: Vec<TodoItem> = todos
        .iter()
        .filter(|t| matches!(t.status, TodoStatus::Pending | TodoStatus::InProgress))
        .cloned()
        .collect();
    if !open.is_empty() {
        let visible: Vec<TodoItem> = open.iter().take(MAX_VISIBLE).cloned().collect();
        let hidden_open_count = open.len().saturating_sub(visible.len());
        return TodoPanelData {
            visible, hidden_open_count, mode: TodoPanelMode::Active,
        };
    }
    let completed: Vec<TodoItem> = todos
        .iter().filter(|t| t.status == TodoStatus::Completed).cloned().collect();
    let visible: Vec<TodoItem> = completed.iter().rev().take(MAX_VISIBLE).cloned().collect();
    TodoPanelData { visible, hidden_open_count: 0, mode: TodoPanelMode::AllCompletedClear }
}
```

**Success Criteria:**
- Returns Active mode when open tasks exist
- Returns AllCompletedClear mode when all done
- Truncates at MAX_VISIBLE (5)
- Reports hidden count for "+N more" hint
- Blocked tasks treated as not-open (treated as completed context)

**Test Plan:**
- active_mode_shows_open_first
- hidden_count_truncates_at_max_visible (10 open → 5 visible, 5 hidden)
- all_done_shows_completed_context (last 3 of completed shown)
- empty_list_returns_empty_panel

**Considerations:**
- Blocked status: oh-my-pi treats as not-open; we follow same convention
- Future: per-task UI for blocked_by[] dep arrows (out of scope)

