**Background:**
The hook is useless without being called. crates/jcode-app-core/src/compaction.rs
has the existing compaction pipeline. Insert call right after context is
compressed.

**Approach:**
```rust
// crates/jcode-app-core/src/compaction.rs
use crate::server::compaction_hooks::restore_todos_after_compaction;

pub async fn compact_session(session_id: &str, messages: &[Message]) -> Result<()> {
    let new_messages = do_compaction(messages).await?;
    // NEW: restore todos from the just-compacted messages
    if let Err(e) = restore_todos_after_compaction(session_id, &new_messages) {
        tracing::warn!("failed to restore todos after compaction: {e}");
    }
    Ok(())
}
```

**Success Criteria:**
- Hook called on every compaction
- Failure does NOT abort compaction (fail-safe with tracing::warn)
- No regression to existing compaction tests

**Test Plan:**
- Existing compaction tests still pass
- Manual: force compaction, verify todos restored in TUI

**Considerations:**
- Compaction runs frequently — keep restore cheap (O(n) message scan is fine for <10k msgs)
- If hook grows expensive, gate behind feature flag

