**Background:**
Reference: claude-code v1 src/utils/sessionRestore.ts:extractTodosFromTranscript.
After context compaction, the model loses todo state from message history even
though the file on disk remains. Scanning transcript ngược (reverse) for the
last TodoWrite tool_use block recovers the most recent todo state.

**Approach:**
New file: crates/jcode-app-core/src/server/compaction_hooks.rs

```rust
pub fn extract_todos_from_transcript(messages: &[serde_json::Value]) -> Vec<TodoItem> {
    for msg in messages.iter().rev() {
        let role = msg.get("role").and_then(|v| v.as_str()).unwrap_or("");
        if role != "assistant" { continue; }
        let content = match msg.get("content") {
            Some(c) if c.is_array() => c.as_array().unwrap(),
            _ => continue,
        };
        for block in content {
            let block_type = block.get("type").and_then(|v| v.as_str()).unwrap_or("");
            let block_name = block.get("name").and_then(|v| v.as_str()).unwrap_or("");
            if block_type == "tool_use" && block_name == "todo" {
                if let Some(input) = block.get("input") {
                    if let Some(todos_raw) = input.get("todos") {
                        return normalize_and_parse(todos_raw);
                    }
                }
            }
        }
    }
    Vec::new()
}

fn normalize_and_parse(raw: &serde_json::Value) -> Vec<TodoItem> {
    // 1. Accept array directly
    // 2. Accept stringified JSON (provider quirk: claude sometimes emits stringified)
    let arr: Vec<serde_json::Value> = if let Some(a) = raw.as_array() {
        a.clone()
    } else if let Some(s) = raw.as_str() {
        match serde_json::from_str::<Vec<serde_json::Value>>(s.trim()) {
            Ok(a) => a,
            Err(_) => return Vec::new(),
        }
    } else { return Vec::new(); };
    arr.into_iter()
        .filter_map(|item| { /* parse content, status, active_form */ })
        .collect()
}
```

**Success Criteria:**
- Returns most recent todo list from transcript
- Handles JSON-as-string quirk (claude tool-call stringification)
- Returns empty Vec when no todo block found
- Skips malformed items (no panic)
- Stops at first hit (reverse scan)

**Test Plan:**
- Unit: extracts_last_todo_block (3 assistant messages, 2 with todo_use, returns last)
- Unit: normalizes_stringified_json
- Unit: empty_when_no_todo_block
- Unit: ignores_user_messages
- Unit: ignores_tool_result_messages
- Unit: skips_malformed_items_gracefully

**Considerations:**
- Performance: O(n) worst case; cache result if scan time > 100ms
- Provider-quirk stringification: documented claude behavior, see jcode comment in tool/todo.rs normalize fn
